798,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,96,Variation across groups motivates estimating a vector of group-specific means rather than a single aggregate.
799,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,97,"ModelsWe evaluate across eight LLMs spanning a range of model families and scales: GPT-5.2, GPT-OSS-20B, Claude Opus 4.6, Claude Sonnet 4.6, Claude Haiku 4.5, Gemini 3.1 Pro Preview, Llama 3 8B Instruct, and Mistral Large 3."
800,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,98,This di- verse set of models allows us to assess performance across families and sizes.
801,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,99,"Each model is prompted to produce offensiveness and politeness ratings on the same statements presented to human annotators, using identical task descriptions and rating scales."
802,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,100,"Full prompt texts and prompting parameters such as temperature are listed in Appendix, Section A."
803,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,101,Evaluation metricsWe evaluate methods in terms ofcoverageandmean absolute error.
804,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,102,Coverage is the empirical rate at which the produced confidence intervals contain the true θ∗ gk.
805,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,103,"Since θ∗ gk is unknown, we approximate it by the group mean computed on the full dataset."
806,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,104,"For PDI and PPI, coverage is provably valid by con- struction for large n (Angelopoulos et al., 2023b); we report it as a sanity check and to evaluate the LLM-only baselines, which have no coverage guar- antees."
807,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,105,"For each estimator, we measure how far its point estimate deviates from the human-rated group mean θ∗ gk, approximated by the full-dataset group mean."
808,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,106,"Specifically, we report the average ab- solute error in percentage points, averaged across demographic groups."
809,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,107,Lower ∆ indicates that the method’s estimates are closer to ground truth on average.
810,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,108,This metric captures estimation accuracy directly in the units of the quantity of interest (per- centage points).
811,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,109,"Coverage asks whether the interval is in the right place, while delta asks whether the estimate itself is."
812,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,110,Metrics are reported across 20 trials. 4 Results 4.1 Politeness In the main text we focus on GPT-5.2 (results with the other models are reported in the Appendix).
813,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,111,"Across prompting variants, the few-shot configura- tion yields the smallest mean prediction error on the politeness task."
814,3,C003_P1_pdf.txt,112,"The subpopulation with the largest error under the best-performing variant is Age 50+, with a few-shot error of 0.426."
