8198,31,C031_P1.txt,1,"Authors: Martin Monperrus ,  Benoit Baudry ,  Clément Vidal   View a PDF of the paper titled Project Rachel: Can an AI Become a Scholarly Author?, by Martin Monperrus and Benoit Baudry and Cl\'ement Vidal View PDF HTML (experimental) Abstract: This paper documents Project Rachel, an action research study that created and tracked a complete AI academic identity named Rachel So."
8199,31,C031_P1.txt,2,"Through careful publication of AI-generated research papers, we investigate how the scholarly ecosystem responds to AI authorship."
8200,31,C031_P1.txt,3,"Rachel So published 10+ papers between March and October 2025, was cited, and received a peer review invitation."
8201,31,C031_P1.txt,4,"We discuss the implications of AI authorship on publishers, researchers, and the scientific system at large."
8202,31,C031_P1.txt,5,"This work contributes empirical action research data to the necessary debate about the future of scholarly communication with super human, hyper capable AI systems."
