10004,36,C036_S1_pdf.txt,156,"(Cynthia, lines 276–280) And, secondly, for generating code from mathematic notation."
10005,36,C036_S1_pdf.txt,157,So I just go by math myself . . .
10006,36,C036_S1_pdf.txt,158,"I explain the problem that I have to ChatGPT using, using math  language, and say, given that I want to formulate this, how would you do it?"
10007,36,C036_S1_pdf.txt,159,"And then  sometimes it’ll give me, it will spit out the first iteration."
10008,36,C036_S1_pdf.txt,160,"(Cynthia, lines 297–299) Another student, Teng, also enlisted ChatGPT for coding, as well as for helping him to  choose appropriate statistical tools for analysing data. . . . with ChatGPT, it will gave me some guidance, and also some clues to start and also, like  I said, also for coding, especially I don’t have any backgrounds for coding and stats, it gave me  lots of clues how to code and how."
10009,36,C036_S1_pdf.txt,161,"(Teng, lines 306–308) In addition to these recognisably technical applications, he was enthusiastic about how it  could help him with academic writing as well as synthesising and summarising informa - tion from academic sources."
10010,36,C036_S1_pdf.txt,162,"However, in his view, it still required human input to make  the most of it."
